08/06/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- The government lifted visa regimes for several Balkan and Central European countries, according to the Albanian Embassy in Warsaw. 
Citizens of Poland, Estonia, Latvia, Lithuania, the Czech Republic, Slovakia, Slovenia, Hungary, Croatia, Romania and Bulgaria are no longer required to have visas to enter Albania. 
The embassy said the move aims to boost economic and cultural relations with these countries, and to open up Albania internationally. 
The move is also being seen as a key step on the road to EU integration. 
(BBC, ATA, Polish news agency, PAP - 06/06/03)
